Gauteng’s crime-fighting initiatives have been given a boost. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The public needs to be harsh on SAPS members that don't take gender-based violence seriously, that's the word from Police Minister Bheki Cele. Cele reiterated that all those who join the police force should prioritise women and children's safety. READ: Cele: South Africans are out to kill He was speaking at the handover of 55 new-high performance vehicles to the Gauteng police.